defs.docs: TCP bindings for `tokio`.

defs.name: Incoming
defs.docs:
Stream returned by the `TcpListener::incoming` function representing the
 stream of sockets received from a listener.

defs.name: TcpListener
defs.docs: An I/O object representing a TCP socket listening for incoming connections.

defs.name: bind
defs.docs: Create a new TCP listener associated with this event loop.

defs.name: poll_accept
defs.docs:
Attempt to accept a connection and create a new connected `TcpStream` if
 successful.

defs.name: poll_accept_std
defs.docs:
Attempt to accept a connection and create a new connected `TcpStream` if
 successful.

defs.name: from_std
defs.docs: Create a new TCP listener from the standard library's TCP listener.

defs.name: local_addr
defs.docs: Returns the local address that this listener is bound to.

defs.name: incoming
defs.docs:
Consumes this listener, returning a stream of the sockets this listener
 accepts.

defs.name: ttl
defs.docs: Gets the value of the `IP_TTL` option for this socket.

defs.name: set_ttl
defs.docs: Sets the value for the `IP_TTL` option on this socket.

defs.name: TcpStream
defs.docs: An I/O object representing a TCP stream connected to a remote endpoint.

defs.name: ConnectFuture
defs.docs:
Future returned by `TcpStream::connect` which will resolve to a `TcpStream`
 when the stream is connected.

defs.name: connect
defs.docs: Create a new TCP stream connected to the specified address.

defs.name: from_std
defs.docs: Create a new `TcpStream` from a `net::TcpStream`.

defs.name: connect_std
defs.docs:
Creates a new `TcpStream` from the pending socket inside the given
 `std::net::TcpStream`, connecting it to the address specified.

defs.name: poll_read_ready
defs.docs: Check the TCP stream's read readiness state.

defs.name: poll_write_ready
defs.docs: Check the TCP stream's write readiness state.

defs.name: local_addr
defs.docs: Returns the local address that this stream is bound to.

defs.name: peer_addr
defs.docs:
Returns the remote address that this stream is connected to.
 # Examples

defs.name: poll_peek
defs.docs:
Receives data on the socket from the remote address to which it is
 connected, without removing that data from the queue. On success,
 returns the number of bytes peeked.

defs.name: shutdown
defs.docs: Shuts down the read, write, or both halves of this connection.

defs.name: nodelay
defs.docs: Gets the value of the `TCP_NODELAY` option on this socket.

defs.name: set_nodelay
defs.docs: Sets the value of the `TCP_NODELAY` option on this socket.

defs.name: recv_buffer_size
defs.docs: Gets the value of the `SO_RCVBUF` option on this socket.

defs.name: set_recv_buffer_size
defs.docs: Sets the value of the `SO_RCVBUF` option on this socket.

defs.name: send_buffer_size
defs.docs: Gets the value of the `SO_SNDBUF` option on this socket.

defs.name: set_send_buffer_size
defs.docs: Sets the value of the `SO_SNDBUF` option on this socket.

defs.name: keepalive
defs.docs:
Returns whether keepalive messages are enabled on this socket, and if so
 the duration of time between them.

defs.name: set_keepalive
defs.docs: Sets whether keepalive messages are enabled to be sent on this socket.

defs.name: ttl
defs.docs: Gets the value of the `IP_TTL` option for this socket.

defs.name: set_ttl
defs.docs: Sets the value for the `IP_TTL` option on this socket.

defs.name: linger
defs.docs:
Reads the linger duration for this socket by getting the `SO_LINGER`
 option.

defs.name: set_linger
defs.docs:
Sets the linger duration of this socket by setting the `SO_LINGER`
 option.

defs.name: try_clone
defs.docs: Creates a new independently owned handle to the underlying socket.
